The rod is an ancient symbol of power and is used when a caster wishes to project their power in order to awe and overwhelm the target. Most rods are not designed to be 
useful as weapons, and are often delicate, but some are quite solid and could be used as a club in an emergency. While a rod could be made from a single piece of straight
wood, most are composed of a shaft and some sort of head, usually constructed of some finer material.
