/IMPLEMENT /ID" ffb7164e-656b-11ee-b520-c87f5455cfcc"/ /IMPLEMENTNAME Holy Symbol IMPLEMENTNAME/
/IMPLEMENTHANDS 1 IMPLEMENTHANDS/ /IMPLEMENTDAMAGE 0 IMPLEMENTDAMAGE/ /IMPLEMENTABILITY WIS IMPLEMENTABILITY/
/IMPLEMENTDESCRIPTION
Spiritual powers often have symbols associated with them, especially those revered as gods by mortals. Such symbols have a potency which belies their often ordinary nature
and believers often use them to focus the power of the spirits they revere to perform mighty magics. Holy symbols must normally be specially blessed and sanctified in order
to be useful.
IMPLEMENTDESCRIPTION/
IMPLEMENT/
/IMPLEMENT /ID" 0f4594fa-656c-11ee-b255-c87f5455cfcc"/ /IMPLEMENTNAME Totem IMPLEMENTNAME/
/IMPLEMENTHANDS 1 IMPLEMENTHANDS/ /IMPLEMENTDAMAGE 2 IMPLEMENTDAMAGE/ /IMPLEMENTABILITY WIS IMPLEMENTABILITY/
/IMPLEMENTDESCRIPTION
Totems are a bit like holy symbols, but they allow the possessor to tune into the natural life force which is present everywhere. Most totems consist of biological material
of some sort, animal or human bones, teeth, claws, hide, or minerals, seeds, etc. Often this material will be contained within a bag or other container, but some totems are
pieces of wood or even just a rock. In order to be potent they must be attuned to nature and the user.
IMPLEMENTDESCRIPTION/
IMPLEMENT/
/IMPLEMENT /ID" 1b982aec-656c-11ee-a517-c87f5455cfcc"/ /IMPLEMENTNAME Knife IMPLEMENTNAME/
